Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi visited Parktown Boys' High on Tuesday morning where he addressed pupils during assembly. JOHANNESBURG Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi has announced he will be convening a meeting with the leadership of all boys schools in the province after a sex abuse scandal hit Parktown Boys' High.Lesufi visited the school on Tuesday morning where he addressed pupils during assembly.This comes after the water polo coach was accused of raping and sexually assaulting more than 20 pupils at the school.The incident came to light after the 22-year-old was caught on the school s CCTV camera, allegedly fondling a 15-year-old pupil in December last year.He was arrested and later released on R3,000 bail.The coach, who has since resigned from the school, appeared in court earlier this month where his case was postponed to July.Lesufi urged pupils to speak out on issues of abuse.He says his department will hold a meeting with all boys schools in the next two weeks.The MEC says a meeting will also be convened with all girls schools in the near future to find ways of addressing issues of abuse at schools.